  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nPlease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use [discord](https://discord.gg/nthXNEv) or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI am noticing that eth_getbalance does not support other blocks than the last one, is this a desired behaviour?\r\n\r\n curl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBalance\",\"params\":[\"0xa1e4380a3b1f749673e270229993ee55f35663b4\", \"0x0\"],\"id\":64}' -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" http://localhost:8545\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":64,\"result\":\"0x39798f8e51d7a12\"}\r\n\r\n curl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBalance\",\"params\":[\"0xa1e4380a3b1f749673e270229993ee55f35663b4\", \"0x19ea66\"],\"id\":64}' -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" http://localhost:8545\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":64,\"result\":\"0x39798f8e51d7a12\"}\r\n\r\nInstead the balance at that block (1698406) should be different, is this a desidered effect? Looking at the API balances for old blocks seem to be supported. \r\n\r\nThank you so much for the amazing work\r\n",
